General John Allen has retired from the military to address health issues within his family, according to a statement from President Obama. The President expressed his appreciation for General Allen's service in Afghanistan and his decades-long service in the Marine Corps. General Allen played a significant role in the growth and capability of Afghan National Security Forces, the degradation of al Qaeda and their allies, and the transition to Afghan security responsibility. He also worked to strengthen the coalition and improve relations with the Afghan government. The President commended General Allen's dedication to the men and women in uniform and their families. He described General Allen as one of America's finest military leaders and a true patriot. The President wished General Allen and his family the best in their new chapter, while assuring that the work led by General Allen in Afghanistan will continue.